<li><a href='http://jamigold.com/2011/01/when-is-a-story-worth-writing-part-two/' rel='bookmark' title='When Is a Story Worth Writing? &#8211; Part Two'>When Is a Story Worth Writing? &#8211; Part Two</a></li>
</ol></p><div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/jamigold?a=8kctihEu1ik:e6avLUWjOgc:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/jamigold?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/jamigold?a=8kctihEu1ik:e6avLUWjOgc:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/jamigold?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/jamigold?a=8kctihEu1ik:e6avLUWjOgc:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/jamigold?i=8kctihEu1ik:e6avLUWjOgc:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/jamigold?a=8kctihEu1ik:e6avLUWjOgc:JUhcmGiK9AQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/jamigold?d=JUhcmGiK9AQ" border="0"></img></a>
